v3:

[$svg_v3_2]*

v4:

[$svg_v4_2]*

## Case 3: symporter with gradients (Na+ 6/1, glucose 2/4, both inward)

v3:

[$svg_v3_3]*

v4:

[$svg_v4_3]*

END_PGML

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

v4 changes vs v3:

- Replaces the two collinear through-pipe arrow segments with an external
  approach arrow + a central binding circle at the waist + a small release
  blob on the far compartment. Visually: approach -> bind -> release.
- Smaller arrowheads (base 3.5 / tip 6 vs v3 base 5 / tip 8).
- Gradient dots become clustered pools; clusters of three or more get a
  rounded-rect pool background.
- Both-inward symporter labels get a 5 px vertical stagger.

